
HXMPP - README
==============
HXMPP is a haXe library for creating XMPP based clients and services.

The library exists in two namespaces:
* xmpp: creation and manipulation of XMPP data.
* jabber: creation and handling of XMPP data streams between jabber entities.



USAGE
-----
Run the hxml files in the base directory to build the included tests, samples, utilities and documentation.
This is NOT required to use the library!
See: hxmpp/samples/* for usage.



COMPILER FLAGS
--------------
* XMPP_DEBUG	Print XMPP transfer
* JABBER_DEBUG	Print verbose debug information
* JABBER_SOCKETBRIDGE	Use a flash socket bridge as stream connection for the javascript target



USING THE BOSH CONNECTION
-------------------------
To use BOSH for connecting you have to proxy you requests.
# Activate mod_proxy apache module
sudo ln -s /etc/apache2/mods-available/proxy.load /etc/apache2/mods-enabled/
# Add following line to proxy.load to activate the proxy-http module
LoadModule proxy_http_module /usr/lib/apache2/modules/mod_proxy_http.so
# Add the proxy directive to the host settings in your http.conf
# This will proxy requests: htp://127.0.0.1/jabber -> http://127.0.0.1:7070/http-bind/
<VirtualHost *:80>
	...
	ProxyRequests Off
	ProxyPass /jabber http://127.0.0.1:7070/http-bind/
	ProxyPassReverse /jabber http://127.0.0.1:7070/http-bind/
	...
</VirtualHost>
# Restart apache
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
#Now you can pass in the path to the constructor of the jabber.BOSHConection class:
var cnx = new BOSHConnection( "domain.net", "localhost/http/" );



SSL/TLS CONNECTIONS
-------------------
Right now secure connections using SSL (at port 5223) are just supported by php and neko.
For neko you have to use the OpenSSL encryption layer from git://83.64.208.21/hxssl.git



USING NODE.JS
-------------
HXMPP has experimental support for node.js through hxNode.
Refer to the documentation of these projects.
http://nodejs.org
http://github.com/blackdog66/hxNode
Tip: The hxml files for the example projects already include node.js target setups but commented out.



XEPS SUPPORTED
--------------

* 0004 DataForms
* 0012 LastActivity
*** 0016 PrivacyLists
* 0030 ServiceDiscovery
** 0045 MUChat
* 0049 Private XML Storage
* 0054 VCardTemp
*** 0060 PubSub
* 0071 XHTML-IM
* 0077 In-Band Registration
* 0082 XMPP Date and Time Profiles
* 0085 ChatStateNotification
* 0092 SoftwareVersion
* 0106 JID Escaping
* 0114 Jabber Component Protocol
** 0115 Entity Capabilities
* 0124 BOSH
** 0163 PersonalEvent 
** 0191 Simple Communications Blocking
* 0199 Ping 
** 0202 EntityTime
* 0203 DelayedDelivery
* 0206 BOSH
*** 0232 Bits of Binary



